title: Data ethics for data scientists, Part 2
description:
Join us for our next session of the RLadiesChch meetup group.

This week we will continue our chat on data ethics based on the pointers shared by UC's Data Science lecturer Giulio Dalla Riva. No matter your subfield or interests, this session will apply to your work, so come for a discussion, for best practice, packages and more!

As usual, we are starting at 5:30, but please note that we are back in our usual venue: E13 on UC's Ilam campus.

title: Practice time for 'Reading and wrangling data in the Tidyverse'
description:
WHERE: E13 in Engineering Core on UC's Ilam campus

This hands-on, group work session allows you to practice the techniques you learnt on Sept 3, in Rogini & Michelle's 'Reading and wrangling data in the Tidyverse' session.

title: Reading and wrangling data in the Tidyverse
description:
>>> Note the slight change in starting time: from September onward the Meetups start at 5:30pm and end at 7:30pm<<<

WHERE: E13 in Engineering Core on UC's Ilam campus

FIRST AND SECOND HOURS (5:30-7:30pm)

Rogini and Michelle will take us from the basics of reading in data in R, all the way to transforming and cleaning it, in preparing it for analysis and visualization.

You can make the most of this session if you come along with a laptop that has both R and RStudio installed and running. Short of that, you are always welcome to come and pair up with someone!

title: Intro to R and RStudio // Reproducibility
description:
WHERE: E13 in Engineering Core on UC's Ilam campus

FIRST HOUR (6-7pm)

Michelle & Rogini introduce us to R and RStudio. No previous R knowledge is assumed, but we expect that
1. you have downloaded R and RStudio on your laptop
2. you attempted to install both R and RStudio (in this order), and
3. you bring your laptop with you
More advanced folks please come along if you can to help the beginners.

SECOND HOUR (7-8pm)

Vica introduces the basic ideas of reproducibility and attempts to make a case that there is no better way to enforce it than in R. Laptop is not necessary for this session.

title: Inaugural planning meeting // Meet and greet
description:
Our first, organizational R-Ladies meetup for all STEAM-gender-minority R / data enthusiasts and professionals in Christchurch.

The meetup will kick off with a meet and greet so we get to hear a bit about what our members are currently doing with data / in R. If you're a complete beginner, don't be shy, tell us what you hope you'll be able to do soon with data!

Vica will bring the outcome of the Google opinion poll, which will serve as a starting point as we discuss how the group envisages future sessions to go. Make sure your wishes are heard, so please fill in the form before the meeting if you haven't done so yet: https://t.co/eRXpYG1tzc

Even if you are only vaguely, tentatively interested, you are very welcome and encouraged to attend (and fill in the poll!). Bring a friend, a mentee or a mentor!

Because this is a social and planning session, there will be no formal presentations, only introductions and open discussions.

Thank you to UC for providing the venue.
